This paper belongs to the sub-category of AI called Neural Networks. 

Explanation: The paper discusses the use of lazy learning in language processing, which involves the use of neural networks to learn from data without explicitly defining rules or abstractions. The author argues that relying too heavily on abstraction can be harmful to the performance of language processing systems, and that lazy learning can be a more effective approach. The paper does not discuss any other sub-categories of AI.
